    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "THE NEW CLIPPER AMERICA\nSTAIRS UNIQUE FEATURE OF CLIPPER AMERICA\nThe Clipper America differs from other airplanes\nas the DC-3 in its time differed from the little\neight-seat planes that preceded it. The spiral\nstairs pictured above mark the liberation of the\npassenger from his seat. Surveys show that the\nimpracticability of moving around in the conventional\nairplane is one of the pet dislikes of the modern\npassenger. The day of immobility is passed. In the\nClipper America, the passenger who tires of the\nupstairs scenery uses these steps to reach the\nspacious lounge on the lower deck.\nPAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS\n135 East 42nd Street\n10011367200\nFor Immediate Release"
    ],
